Sentencas: Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-delta (SFM) perovskite is carefully investigated as an anode material for solid oxide fuel cells with LaGaO3-based electrolytes.
Titulo: Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ - Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 Composite Anodes for Intermediate-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Its electronic conductivity under anodic atmosphere is measured with four-probe method while its ionic conductivity is determined with oxygen permeation measurement.
Titulo: Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ - Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 Composite Anodes for Intermediate-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Samaria doped ceria (SDC) is incorporated into SFM electrode to improve the anodic performance.
Titulo: Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ - Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 Composite Anodes for Intermediate-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: A strong relation is observed between SDC addition and polarization losses, suggesting that the internal SFM-SDC contacts are active for H-2 oxidation.
Titulo: Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ - Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 Composite Anodes for Intermediate-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The best electrode performance is achieved for the composite with 30 wt% SDC addition, resulting in an interfacial polarization resistance of 0.258 Omega cm(2) at 700 degrees C for La0.8Sr0.2Ga0.8Mg0.2O3-delta supported single cells.
Titulo: Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ - Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 Composite Anodes for Intermediate-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Electrochemical impedance spectroscopy analysis indicates that the high performance of SFM-SDC composite anodes is likely due to the high ionic conductivity and electro-catalytic activity of SDC by promoting the ionic exchange processes.
Titulo: Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ - Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 Composite Anodes for Intermediate-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Redox cycle treatment shows that SDC addition can even improve the redox tolerance of SFM anodes.
Titulo: Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ - Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 Composite Anodes for Intermediate-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
